  "root_text": {
    "sn2.8:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 2.8 ",
    "sn2.8:0.2": "1. Paṭhamavagga ",
    "sn2.8:0.3": "Tāyanasutta ",
    "sn2.8:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn2.8:1.2": "Atha kho tāyano devaputto purāṇatitthakaro abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṁ jetavanaṁ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ aṭṭhāsi. ",
    "sn2.8:1.3": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhito kho tāyano devaputto bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
    "sn2.8:2.1": "“Chinda sotaṁ parakkamma, ",
    "sn2.8:2.2": "kāme panuda brāhmaṇa; ",
    "sn2.8:2.3": "Nappahāya munī kāme, ",
    "sn2.8:2.4": "nekattamupapajjati. ",
    "sn2.8:3.1": "Kayirā ce kayirāthenaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:3.2": "daḷhamenaṁ parakkame; ",
    "sn2.8:3.3": "Sithilo hi paribbājo, ",
    "sn2.8:3.4": "bhiyyo ākirate rajaṁ. ",
    "sn2.8:4.1": "Akataṁ dukkaṭaṁ seyyo, ",
    "sn2.8:4.2": "pacchā tapati dukkaṭaṁ; ",
    "sn2.8:4.3": "Katañca sukataṁ seyyo, ",
    "sn2.8:4.4": "yaṁ katvā nānutappati. ",
    "sn2.8:5.1": "Kuso yathā duggahito, ",
    "sn2.8:5.2": "hatthamevānukantati; ",
    "sn2.8:5.3": "Sāmaññaṁ dupparāmaṭṭhaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:5.4": "nirayāyūpakaḍḍhati. ",
    "sn2.8:6.1": "Yaṁ kiñci sithilaṁ kammaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:6.2": "saṅkiliṭṭhañca yaṁ vataṁ; ",
    "sn2.8:6.3": "Saṅkassaraṁ brahmacariyaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:6.4": "na taṁ hoti mahapphalan”ti. ",
    "sn2.8:7.1": "Idamavoca tāyano devaputto; ",
    "sn2.8:7.2": "idaṁ vatvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṁ katvā tatthevantaradhāyīti. ",
    "sn2.8:8.1": "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
    "sn2.8:8.2": "“imaṁ, bhikkhave, rattiṁ tāyano nāma devaputto purāṇatitthakaro abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṁ jetavanaṁ obhāsetvā yenāhaṁ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ aṭṭhāsi. ",
    "sn2.8:8.3": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhito kho, bhikkhave, tāyano devaputto mama santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
    "sn2.8:9.1": "‘Chinda sotaṁ parakkamma, ",
    "sn2.8:9.2": "kāme panuda brāhmaṇa; ",
    "sn2.8:9.3": "Nappahāya munī kāme, ",
    "sn2.8:9.4": "nekattamupapajjati. ",
    "sn2.8:10.1": "Kayirā ce kayirāthenaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:10.2": "daḷhamenaṁ parakkame; ",
    "sn2.8:10.3": "Sithilo hi paribbājo, ",
    "sn2.8:10.4": "bhiyyo ākirate rajaṁ. ",
    "sn2.8:11.1": "Akataṁ dukkaṭaṁ seyyo, ",
    "sn2.8:11.2": "pacchā tapati dukkaṭaṁ; ",
    "sn2.8:11.3": "Katañca sukataṁ seyyo, ",
    "sn2.8:11.4": "yaṁ katvā nānutappati. ",
    "sn2.8:12.1": "Kuso yathā duggahito, ",
    "sn2.8:12.2": "hatthamevānukantati; ",
    "sn2.8:12.3": "Sāmaññaṁ dupparāmaṭṭhaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:12.4": "nirayāyūpakaḍḍhati. ",
    "sn2.8:13.1": "Yaṁ kiñci sithilaṁ kammaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:13.2": "saṅkiliṭṭhañca yaṁ vataṁ; ",
    "sn2.8:13.3": "Saṅkassaraṁ brahmacariyaṁ, ",
    "sn2.8:13.4": "na taṁ hoti mahapphalan’ti. ",
    "sn2.8:14.1": "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, tāyano devaputto, idaṁ vatvā maṁ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṁ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi. ",
    "sn2.8:14.2": "Uggaṇhātha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā; ",
    "sn2.8:14.3": "pariyāpuṇātha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā; ",
    "sn2.8:14.4": "dhāretha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā. ",
    "sn2.8:14.5": "Atthasaṁhitā, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā ādibrahmacariyikā”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn2.8:0.1": "Linked Discourses 2.8 ",
    "sn2.8:0.2": "Chapter One ",
    "sn2.8:0.3": "With Tāyana ",
    "sn2.8:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn2.8:1.2": "Then, late at night, the glorious godling Tāyana, formerly a religious founder, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, ",
    "sn2.8:1.3": "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: ",
    "sn2.8:2.1": "“Cut the stream after striving! ",
    "sn2.8:2.2": "Cast aside sensual pleasures, brahmin. ",
    "sn2.8:2.3": "A sage who doesn’t give up sensual pleasures ",
    "sn2.8:2.4": "is not reborn in a unified state. ",
    "sn2.8:3.1": "If one is to do what should be done, ",
    "sn2.8:3.2": "one should staunchly strive. ",
    "sn2.8:3.3": "For the life gone forth when laxly led ",
    "sn2.8:3.4": "just stirs up dust all the more. ",
    "sn2.8:4.1": "A bad deed is better left undone, ",
    "sn2.8:4.2": "for it will plague you later on. ",
    "sn2.8:4.3": "A good deed is better done, ",
    "sn2.8:4.4": "one that does not plague you. ",
    "sn2.8:5.1": "When kusa grass is wrongly grasped ",
    "sn2.8:5.2": "it only cuts the hand. ",
    "sn2.8:5.3": "So too, the ascetic life, when wrongly taken, ",
    "sn2.8:5.4": "drags you to hell. ",
    "sn2.8:6.1": "Any lax act, ",
    "sn2.8:6.2": "any corrupt observance, ",
    "sn2.8:6.3": "or suspicious spiritual life, ",
    "sn2.8:6.4": "is not very fruitful.” ",
    "sn2.8:7.1": "That’s what the godling Tāyana said. ",
    "sn2.8:7.2": "Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there. ",
    "sn2.8:8.1": "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha told the mendicants all that had happened. ",
    "sn2.8:8.2": "“Mendicants, tonight, the glorious godling Tāyana, formerly a religious founder, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, came to me, bowed, stood to one side, ",
    "sn2.8:8.3": "and recited these verses in my presence.” The Buddha repeated the verses in full, adding: ",
    "sn2.8:9.1": "",
    "sn2.8:9.2": "",
    "sn2.8:9.3": "",
    "sn2.8:9.4": "",
    "sn2.8:10.1": "",
    "sn2.8:10.2": "",
    "sn2.8:10.3": "",
    "sn2.8:10.4": "",
    "sn2.8:11.1": "",
    "sn2.8:11.2": "",
    "sn2.8:11.3": "",
    "sn2.8:11.4": "",
    "sn2.8:12.1": "",
    "sn2.8:12.2": "",
    "sn2.8:12.3": "",
    "sn2.8:12.4": "",
    "sn2.8:13.1": "",
    "sn2.8:13.2": "",
    "sn2.8:13.3": "",
    "sn2.8:13.4": "",
    "sn2.8:14.1": "“That’s what the godling Tāyana said. Then he bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right side, before vanishing right there. ",
    "sn2.8:14.2": "Mendicants, learn the verses of Tāyana! ",
    "sn2.8:14.3": "Memorize the verses of Tāyana! ",
    "sn2.8:14.4": "Remember the verses of Tāyana! ",
    "sn2.8:14.5": "These verses are beneficial and relate to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.” "
  },
